{"type":"message","id":"13db65be","parentId":"f79f4764","timestamp":"2026-03-03T11:31:38.069Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_vyaoxfm3xaw9_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"execution_id\": \"efbb3824-5822-4bb4-a68a-9bae88d17920\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"status_code\": 200,\n    \"message\": \"Result content is too long (72809 bytes). You can reference the truncated content (20480 bytes) and download the full content from the url provided.\",\n    \"full_content_file_url\": \"http://qveris-tool-results-cache-bj.oss-cn-beijing.aliyuncs.com/tool_result_cache%2F20260303%2Falphavantage.news_sentiment.retrieve.v1.7aca3c4a%2F237461074d704eca899afaf35aa165f8.json?OSSAccessKeyId=LTAI5tM3qNRZSgSrg1iSTALm&Expires=1772544696&Signature=rtzigZcpVwWvuSeJBabHpk3of4U%3D\",\n    \"truncated_content\": \"{\\\"items\\\": \\\"50\\\", \\\"sentiment_score_definition\\\": \\\"x <= -0.35: Bearish; -0.35 < x <= -0.15: Somewhat-Bearish; -0.15 < x < 0.15: Neutral; 0.15 <= x < 0.35: Somewhat_Bullish; x >= 0.35: Bullish\\\", \\\"relevance_score_definition\\\": \\\"0 < x <= 1, with a higher score indicating higher relevance.\\\", \\\"feed\\\": [{\\\"title\\\": \\\"XPO’s tonnage turns positive in February\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.freightwaves.com/news/xpos-tonnage-turns-positive-in-february\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T105927\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [\\\"Todd Maiden\\\"], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"XPO announced that its tonnage returned to positive territory in February 2026, marking the first time since June 2024. The less-than-truckload carrier reported a 0.2% year-over-year increase in tonnage, driven by a 3% rise in daily shipments despite a decline in weight per shipment. This positive trend aligns with favorable manufacturing data and the company's strategic initiatives, including adding local accounts and expanding services, positioning XPO for expected operating margin improvement in the first quarter.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://freightwaves.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/02/An-XPO-trailer-at-a-terminal.jpg?resize=970,546&width=970&height=546\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"FreightWaves\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"FreightWaves\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"earnings\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.924748\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"economy_macro\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.834682\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"energy_transportation\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.941592\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"manufacturing\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.832568\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.42521, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Bullish\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"XPO\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.419074\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Bullish\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"XLE ETF Holdings List — AMEX:XLE\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.tradingview.com/symbols/AMEX-XLE/holdings/\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T105920\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"This article lists the top holdings of the XLE (State Street Energy Select Sector SPDR ETF) as of February 27, 2026. Key holdings include Exxon Mobil Corporation, Chevron Corporation, and ConocoPhillips, comprising significant percentages of the fund's composition. The list provides details on the weight, shares, and market value for each of the top ten held companies.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://s3-symbol-logo.tradingview.com/sector/energy--big.svg\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"TradingView\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"TradingView\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.915644\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"energy_transportation\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.845130\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.044461, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"XLE\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.039025\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"XOM\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.948267\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.014748\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"CVX\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.852006\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.020518\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"COP\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.789206\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.012838\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"WMB\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.669133\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.037264\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"State Street SPDR S&P Emerging Markets ex-China ETF Holdings\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.quiverquant.com/etf/State%20Street%20SPDR%20S&P%20Emerging%20Markets%20ex-China%20ETF\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T105856\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"The article provides a detailed list of the holdings for the State Street SPDR S&P Emerging Markets ex-China ETF (XCNY). Established on September 4, 2024, by State Street, this ETF focuses on a market cap-weighted index of emerging market stocks, excluding those from China. The fund aims for broad diversification and includes companies of various market capitalizations, with Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Co. being its largest reported holding.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": null, \\\"source\\\": \\\"Quiver Quantitative\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"Quiver Quantitative\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.931525\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.321219, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Somewhat-Bullish\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"XCNY\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.323873\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Somewhat-Bullish\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"XHLF Stock Fund Price and Chart — AMEX:XHLF\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.tradingview.com/symbols/AMEX-XHLF/\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T105854\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"This article provides comprehensive information on the BondBloxx Bloomberg Six Month Target Duration US Treasury ETF (XHLF), detailing its price movements, key statistics like AUM and dividend yield, and investment strategy. It covers the fund's composition, management, and performance, alongside technical analysis ratings and frequently asked questions about ETFs.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://s3-symbol-logo.tradingview.com/bondbloxx--big.svg\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"TradingView\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"TradingView\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"finance\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.939326\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": -0.130655, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"XHLF\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"-0.102306\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"$1M bet on mining wastewater: Cetos Water wins Wheaton sustainability prize\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.stocktitan.net/news/WPM/wheaton-precious-metals-announces-cetos-water-as-the-winner-of-its-3t7rouaflkey.html\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T105832\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Wheaton Precious Metals has awarded Cetos Water US$1 million for its innovative low-energy, solvent-based technology that converts mining wastewater into reusable water. This award is part of Wheaton's second annual Future of Mining Challenge, which aims to identify sustainable solutions for the mining industry. Cetos Water's technology is recognized for its potential to significantly improve water management and environmental outcomes in mining operations globally.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": null, \\\"source\\\": \\\"Stock Titan\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"Stock Titan\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"technology\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.819862\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"finance\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.743727\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"economy_macro\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.630280\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.309589, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Somewhat-Bullish\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"WPM\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.314363\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Somewhat-Bullish\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Technical Analysis of Teucrium Wheat Fund ETV (AMEX:WEAT)\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.tradingview.com/symbols/AMEX-WEAT/technicals/\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T105802\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"This article provides a technical analysis of the Teucrium Wheat Fund ETV (AMEX:WEAT), presenting a summary of technical indicators including moving averages, oscillators, and pivots across various timeframes. It explains what these indicators mean and how they can be used for trading decisions, highlighting that while the overall technical rating for WEAT is currently \\\\\\\"buy,\\\\\\\" market conditions constantly change, and the 1-week and 1-month ratings suggest neutral and sell trends respectively. The article advises against making investment decisions solely based on these ratings and encourages users to consider additional information and news.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://s3-symbol-logo.tradingview.com/teucrium-agricultural--big.svg\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"TradingView\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"TradingView\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.904312\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.098537, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"WEAT\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.061573\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Advisorshares Vice Etf Stock Price Forecast. Should You Buy ACT?\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://stockinvest.us/stock/ACT\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T105758\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"This article provides a stock analysis and forecast for Advisorshares Vice Etf (ACT), indicating it as a \\\\\\\"Buy or Hold\\\\\\\" candidate since February 2, 2026. The stock closed at $42.44 on March 2, 2026, and is projected to rise by 9.43% in the next three months. The analysis highlights positive technical signals such as buy signals from moving averages and increasing volume alongside price, while also noting some negative signals like a recent pivot top.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": null, \\\"source\\\": \\\"StockInvest.us\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"StockInvest.us\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.940001\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"earnings\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.810741\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.042664, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"VICE\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.322454\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.032987\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Xtant Medical Holdings receives USD 10.7M from Companion Spine\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://medicalbuyer.co.in/xtant-medical-holdings-receives-usd-10-7m-from-companion-spine/\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T105715\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Xtant Medical Holdings received an additional $10.7 million from Companion Spine, finalizing the total aggregate purchase price of $21.4 million for the sale of Coflex® assets and Paradigm OUS businesses. This payment includes $8.2 million for an unsecured promissory note and $2.2 million from working capital and other adjustments. Xtant Medical plans to use these funds to reduce long-term debt and increase cash liquidity, allowing them to focus on their higher-margin biologics business.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://medicalbuyer.co.in/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Xtant-Medical-Holdings-receives-USD-10.7M-from-Companion-Spine-n.png\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"Medical Buyer\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"Medical Buyer\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"mergers_and_acquisitions\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.921728\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"earnings\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.801569\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"life_sciences\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.736363\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.470542, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Bullish\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"XTNT\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.480631\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Bullish\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"3 Financials Stocks Worth Your Attention\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://finviz.com/news/327862/3-financials-stocks-worth-your-attention\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T105013\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [\\\"Anthony Lee\\\"], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"The financial industry has faced challenges with a 7.1% tumble over the past six months, contrasting with the S&P 500's 6.6% return. Despite this, the article highlights three financial stocks—Synchrony Financial (SYF), EVERTEC (EVTC), and American Express (AXP)—that are recommended for their potential to generate sustainable market-beating returns due to strong earnings growth, efficient management, and appealing valuations. Each company's performance metrics and valuation ratios are presented as reasons for investor attention.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://news-assets.stockstory.org/cover-images/_1400x700_crop_center-center_none/synchrony-financial-cover-image-31b3b325532a_2025-08-18-180007_ugdw.jpeg\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"Finviz\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"Finviz\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"earnings\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.930188\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.809899\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"finance\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.913862\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.360234, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Bullish\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"SYF\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.440210\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Bullish\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"AXP\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.847749\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.436901\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Bullish\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"PLTR\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.631015\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.326948\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Somewhat-Bullish\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"NVDA\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.594493\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.340120\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Somewhat-Bullish\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Robotaxi fleet suspended in Dubai as Gulf conflict intensifies\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/weride-taxi-dubai-iran-pony-ai-b2930870.html\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T104942\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [\\\"Brenda Goh\\\", \\\"Qiaoyi Li\\\", \\\"Zhang Yan\\\"], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Chinese autonomous driving firm WeRide has suspended its robotaxi fleet in Dubai due to the escalating US-Israel conflict with Iran, impacting a promising market for robotaxi companies. While Dubai operations are halted and employees are working from home, WeRide’s fleets in Abu Dhabi and Riyadh continue normal operations. Other major Chinese robotaxi firms like Baidu's Apollo Go and Pony.ai are also monitoring the situation and adjusting services as needed.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://static.independent.co.uk/2026/03/03/10/24/FILE-PHOTO-WeRide-autonomous-taxi-is-seen-in-Guangzhou-ztnt3p1p.jpeg\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"The Independent\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"The Independent\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"energy_transportation\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.943417\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"technology\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.839582\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": -0.110069, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"WRD\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.311847\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.031563\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"UBER\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.719328\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"-0.247989\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Somewhat-Bearish\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Miller Investment Management LP Decreases Stake in JPMorgan Chase & Co. $JPM\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.marketbeat.com/instant-alerts/filing-miller-investment-management-lp-decreases-stake-in-jpmorgan-chase-co-jpm-2026-03-03/\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T104941\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [\\\"MarketBeat\\\"], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Miller Investment Management LP significantly reduced its stake in JPMorgan Chase & Co. (NYSE:JPM) by 39.7% in the third quarter, selling 7,525 shares and retaining 11,410 shares valued at approximately $3.60 million. Despite this reduction from one hedge fund, other institutional investors have increased their holdings, and institutions collectively own 71.55% of JPM stock. Analysts maintain a \\\\\\\"Moderate Buy\\\\\\\" consensus rating for JPM with an average price target of $339.55, following a strong Q4 earnings report where the company beat EPS expectations.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://www.marketbeat.com/logos/jpmorgan-chase--co-logo-1200x675.png?v=20221020142040\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"MarketBeat\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"MarketBeat\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"earnings\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.917080\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.806782\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"finance\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.724214\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"economy_macro\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.601703\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.05355, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"JPM\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"-0.072309\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"AVGO\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.602844\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.136179\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}, {\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"PYPL\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.561920\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.003358\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Fox Run Management L.L.C. Sells 6,848 Shares of Leidos Holdings, Inc. $LDOS\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.marketbeat.com/instant-alerts/filing-fox-run-management-llc-sells-6848-shares-of-leidos-holdings-inc-ldos-2026-03-03/\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T104749\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [\\\"MarketBeat\\\"], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Fox Run Management L.L.C. has reduced its stake in Leidos Holdings, Inc. (NYSE:LDOS) by 82.4%, selling 6,848 shares and retaining 1,460 shares valued at approximately $276,000. Leidos recently reported quarterly earnings of $2.76 per share, beating estimates, and announced a quarterly dividend of $0.43. The company's stock has an average rating of \\\\\\\"Moderate Buy\\\\\\\" from analysts, with an average target price of $214.18.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://www.marketbeat.com/logos/leidos-holdings-inc-logo-1200x675.jpg\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"MarketBeat\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"MarketBeat\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"earnings\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.929844\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.846206\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"finance\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.743424\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"economy_macro\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.621494\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"technology\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.634570\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": -0.089142, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"LDOS\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"-0.079468\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Vornado Realty Trust $VNO Shares Sold by Fox Run Management L.L.C.\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.marketbeat.com/instant-alerts/filing-vornado-realty-trust-vno-shares-sold-by-fox-run-management-llc-2026-03-03/\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T104747\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [\\\"MarketBeat\\\"], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Fox Run Management L.L.C. significantly reduced its stake in Vornado Realty Trust (NYSE:VNO) by 85.1% in the third quarter, selling 39,900 shares and retaining 7,012 shares. Despite missing EPS estimates, Vornado reported higher-than-expected revenue. The stock trades near $27.40, has a P/E of 6.54, a market cap of $5.22 billion, and recently paid an annual dividend of $0.74 per share.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://www.marketbeat.com/logos/vornado-realty-trust-logo-1200x675.jpg?v=20240424115714\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"MarketBeat\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"MarketBeat\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"earnings\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.924768\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"real_estate\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.920844\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.733581\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.026198, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"VNO-P-N\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.303071\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.014546\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Neutral\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Intech Investment Management LLC Raises Holdings in Stryker Corporation $SYK\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.marketbeat.com/instant-alerts/filing-intech-investment-management-llc-raises-holdings-in-stryker-corporation-syk-2026-03-03/\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T104731\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [\\\"MarketBeat\\\"], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Intech Investment Management LLC significantly increased its stake in Stryker Corporation (NYSE:SYK) by 47% in the third quarter of 2025, now holding 8,784 shares valued at $3.25 million. This move is part of a broader trend of institutional investment, with firms like Norges Bank and Alliancebernstein L.P. also holding substantial positions, leading to institutional investors owning 77.09% of the medical technology company's stock. Despite a director's sale of shares, analysts maintain a \\\\\\\"Moderate Buy\\\\\\\" consensus rating with a price target of $426.47, following Stryker's strong quarterly earnings beat and dividend announcement.\\\", \\\"banner_image\\\": \\\"https://www.marketbeat.com/logos/stryker-logo-1200x675.png\\\", \\\"source\\\": \\\"MarketBeat\\\", \\\"category_within_source\\\": \\\"General\\\", \\\"source_domain\\\": \\\"MarketBeat\\\", \\\"topics\\\": [{\\\"topic\\\": \\\"earnings\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.917484\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"finance\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.807488\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"financial_markets\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.848283\\\"}, {\\\"topic\\\": \\\"life_sciences\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"0.744576\\\"}], \\\"overall_sentiment_score\\\": 0.441333, \\\"overall_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Bullish\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment\\\": [{\\\"ticker\\\": \\\"SYK\\\", \\\"relevance_score\\\": \\\"1.000000\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_score\\\": \\\"0.418106\\\", \\\"ticker_sentiment_label\\\": \\\"Bullish\\\"}]}, {\\\"title\\\": \\\"Intech Investment Management LLC Buys 32,575 Shares of Trimble Inc. $TRMB\\\", \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.marketbeat.com/instant-alerts/filing-intech-investment-management-llc-buys-32575-shares-of-trimble-inc-trmb-2026-03-03/\\\", \\\"time_published\\\": \\\"20260303T104729\\\", \\\"authors\\\": [\\\"MarketBeat\\\"], \\\"summary\\\": \\\"Intech Investment Management LLC significantly increased its stake in T\",\n    \"content_schema\": {\n      \"$schema\": \"http://json-schema.org/schema#\",\n      \"type\": \"object\",\n      \"properties\": {\n        \"items\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        \"sentiment_score_definition\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        \"relevance_score_definition\": {\n          \"type\": \"string\"\n        },\n        \"feed\": {\n          \"type\": \"array\",\n          \"items\": {\n            \"type\": \"object\",\n            \"properties\": {\n          